+# PR-214 Remediation Report
+
+## Thread Classification
+
+- `T-214-01`: actionable
+- `T-214-02`: duplicate of `T-214-01`
+- `T-214-03`: obsolete outdated hunk suggestion
+- `T-214-04`: actionable
+- `T-214-05`: actionable
+
+The authoritative classification is recorded in
+`artifacts/review/thread_triage.json`.
+
+## Code Remediation
+
+Updated `src/policy/approval_router.py` so `build_policy_preview(...)`
+normalizes the incoming approval state before it calls
+`build_preview_payload(...)`.
+
+Updated `src/policy/preview.py` so the fallback payload for
+`preview_enabled=False` retains:
+
+- `approval_state`
+- `requires_human_review`
+
+This preserves the expected behavior for:
+
+`build_policy_preview(request_id=..., preview_enabled=False, approval_state="manual_review", actor=...)`
+
+The resulting payload now keeps:
+
+- `approval_state="human_review_required"`
+- `requires_human_review=true`
+
+No legacy preview alias or `legacy_preview_hint` field was added.
+
+## Test and Doc Updates
+
+Updated `tests/test_preview.py` with a regression test for the fallback/manual
+review normalization path.
+
+Updated `docs/approval_policy.md` so the fallback response example now shows:
+
+```json
+{
+  "request_id": "req-214",
+  "status": "preview_unavailable",
+  "actor": "review-bot",
+  "approval_state": "human_review_required",
+  "requires_human_review": true
+}
+```
+
+## Verification
+
+Executed:
+
+```bash
+python3 -m pytest tests/test_preview.py tests/test_approval_router.py
+```
+
+Result: `5 passed`
